        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The speech channel that has finished processing input text.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "chan"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The reference constant associated with the speech channel. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "refCon"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The number of bytes between the beginning of the text buffer and the beginning of the word about to be pronounced. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "wordPos"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The length in bytes of the word about to be pronounced. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "wordLen"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Speech Synthesis Manager calls a speech channel’s wordcallback function just before it pronounces a word. You might usesuch a callback function, for example, to draw the word about tobe spoken in a window. In this case, the callback function wouldset a global flag variable to indicate that the word being spokenis changing and another two global variables to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "wordPos",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "wordLen",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".A function called by your application’s main event loop coulddetect that the word being spoken is changing and draw the wordin a window.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can specify a word callback function by passing the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "soWordCallBack",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " selectorto the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
